Emergency Service
Emergency service is available 24 hours a day. To report water outages please contact Del-Co at either the toll free
number (800)521-6779 or the local number (740)548-7746.
Important Information
· Vacant properties are issued a minimum water bill where service is available.
· An actual reading is taken every month weather permitting. Estimates, if necessary are based on your previous
average consumption.
· Rate schedules are available at our office and at www.delcowater.org
· Del-Co does not issue credits toward water usage for lawn irrigation.
· Only payments should be mailed to the Post Office Box. Please send all other correspondence to the
Del-Co Water Office.
· Del-Co reserves the right to present checks electronically at first presentment or any re-presentment by transmitting
the amount of the check, routing number, account number, and serial number to your financial institution.
· Account is considered paid when payment is received in the Del-Co Water Offices. Del-Co Water is not responsible
for mail service or electronic transactions.
· Failure to receive a bill does not relieve responsibility for payment when it is due.
· There is a $20 charge for checks/ACH returned from a bank for any reason.
Delinquent Account Information
A delinquent notice will be mailed to the customer if the amount due on the account has not been paid in full by the due
date of a regular invoice. Failure to pay past due balances may result in additional fees and the disconnection of water
service. Receiving a regular invoice after a delinquent notice has been issued does not change the disconnect date
indicated on the delinquent notice. Please notify Del-Co Water of payments made toward delinquent accounts. Should
the water service to a delinquent property be disconnected the delinquent account balance and all associated fees must
be paid in full before water service is restored. Water service may not be restored
the same day it was disconnected.
